main event: A bright white object was observed in the sky over Alamosa, Colorado on October 21, 1965.
interesting points: The object was round in shape and had a brief flash of bright white color.
The observers believed the object was similar to an aircraft or rocket based on the color and lack of sound.
There was no distinct trail or fragmentation data observed.
The sighting only lasted for about 2 seconds.
The preliminary analysis indicated the object was likely a meteorite.
